dataset_id: Gridded Population of the World, Version 4 (GPWv4): National Identifier Grid
title: Gridded Population of the World, Version 4 (GPWv4): National Identifier Grid
summary: The Gridded Population of the World, Version 4 (GPWv4): National Identifier Grid is derived from the input census units to create a raster surface where pixels (grid cells) that cover the same census data source - most often a country or territory - have the same value. Note that these data represent the area covered by the statistical data as provided, and are not official representations of country or territory boundaries.
